# Trivy CVE suppression file.
# Format: one CVE ID per line, optionally with an expiry date and justification.
#
# Example:
#   CVE-2021-44228  # Log4Shell — not applicable, no Log4j dependency
#   CVE-2023-99999 exp:2026-12-31  # accepted risk; mitigation: WAF rule ABC-123
#
# Process to add a suppression:
#   1. Open a risk-acceptance ticket linked to the CVE
#   2. Append the CVE ID below with a one-line justification (and expiry date if a temporary waiver)
#   3. Reference the ticket in the commit message
#   4. Re-run CI to verify the suppression takes effect
#
# Audit rule: every entry without `exp:` is a permanent waiver and must have an annual review.
# Active suppressions list:
#   (none)
